'Case' implementation for the <a href='http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html' title='JDK class in java.util.regex'>Pattern</a> class, which allows
testing a String against a number of regular expressions.
For example:
<pre>switch( str ) {
  case ~/one/ :
    // the regex 'one' matches the value of str
}
</pre>
Note that this returns true for the case where both the pattern and
the 'switch' values are <code>null</code>.
